## Workflow

This project follows Spec-Driven Development (SDD) + verification-driven delivery.

Recommended order:

1. Fill in `docs/workflow/00-intake/README.md`
2. Define `docs/workflow/01-requirements/README.md`
3. Produce `docs/workflow/02-design/README.md`
4. Capture long-lived truth under `docs/knowledge/`
5. Break down `docs/workflow/03-implementation/README.md`
6. Define `docs/workflow/04-verification/README.md`
7. Generate `docs/workflow/05-tasks/README.md`
8. Create `docs/changes/active/<change-key>/` for the current work
9. Review `docs/rules/README.md`
10. Start implementation and keep tests and docs in sync

## Document Guide

- `docs/workflow/00-intake/README.md`: background, users, goals, non-goals
- `docs/workflow/01-requirements/README.md`: current delivery requirements, what / why only
- `docs/workflow/02-design/README.md`: current-stage design, how only
- `docs/workflow/03-implementation/README.md`: milestones, order, dependencies
- `docs/workflow/04-verification/README.md`: verification strategy and requirement-to-test mapping
- `docs/workflow/05-tasks/README.md`: executable task list
- `docs/knowledge/context/README.md`: glossary, actors, entities, and business boundaries
- `docs/knowledge/structure/README.md`: module boundaries, system structure, and integrations
- `docs/knowledge/behavior/README.md`: key flows, state transitions, and rules
- `docs/knowledge/reference/README.md`: examples, schemas, fixtures, assets, and fixed references
- `docs/issues/README.md`: unresolved issues, blockers, risks, and technical debt
- `docs/changes/README.md`: change-layer overview and archival rules
- `docs/changes/active/`: active change workspaces
- `docs/releases/README.md`: release history
- `docs/archive/README.md`: archived and deprecated document index
- `docs/adr/README.md`: decision record index
- `docs/rules/README.md`: coding, testing, doc-sync, and Definition of Done rules
- `docs/rules/document-routing-rules.md`: semantic-to-path routing rules for documents
- `docs/rules/change-management-rules.md`: change-tracking and release rules
- `docs/rules/issue-management-rules.md`: issue tracking and document retirement rules
- `docs/rules/clarification-rules.md`: clarification and decision confirmation rules
- `docs/rules/bug-fix-rules.md`: bug fixing, root-cause, and regression rules
- `spec-init.topology.yml`: the project's current document topology and default routing map

## Traceability

The project should maintain at least this chain:

- `FR-*` defines requirements
- `DES-*` defines how the requirements are satisfied
- `TEST-*` defines how the requirements are verified
- `T-*` defines the execution tasks

Before implementation starts, confirm at least one complete chain:

`FR-001 -> DES-001 -> TEST-001 -> T-001`

